## Key Rules

### Build & Test

- Use `{{CLI_ENTRYPOINT}}` for all build, test, lint, and deploy operations.
- Never run ecosystem tools directly (`cargo`, `npm`, `go`, `python`, `docker compose`).
- All commands must produce full, unfiltered output — no piping through `head`, `tail`, or filters.

### Code Quality

- No default values, fallbacks, or stubs in production code.
- No dead code, `TODO` comments, or `unimplemented!()` markers.
- No commented-out code — git has history.
- Every public function must be tested.

### File Operations

- Use IDE file tools (create_file, replace_string_in_file) for all file writes.
- Never use shell redirection (`>`, `>>`, `tee`, heredoc-to-file) to write files.

